  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development and its findings are discussed in the UQ narrative. All 13 credibility factors are assessed. Decision: Accepted. Note: the structured hasSensitivityAnalysis link was not encoded in this package; dominant input drivers therefore remain uncharacterized at the structured evidence level despite the verbal reference to screening.",
